"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-sport-team-gb-kit-paris-olympics-2024-adidas-tom-daley-max-whitlock-b1152355.html\", \"text\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies. Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search. See our privacy policy for more information.  Sport  This is the first look at the kitBritain'sathleteswill wear at this year'sOlympicand Paralympic Games in Paris.  The design byAdidasis described as \\\"grounded in simplicity\\\" and \\\"builds around the classic British red, white and blue\\\" while featuring \\\"white lion head graphics\\\". The \\\"sleek, modern collection\\\" is designed so the red and white elements pop against the blue when athletes are competing.  Among those modelling the kit were gymnastMax Whitlockand divers Andrea Spendolini-Sirieix - daughter of First Dates host Fred Sirieix - andTom Daley.  Daley, who first competed at the 2008 Olympics and won his first medal at the 2012 London Games, said: \\\"Heading into my fifth Olympics, I can genuinely say nothing compares to competing in myTeam GBkit, knowing that all the training I have done is gearing towards hopefully winning a medal for my country.  \\\"This new kit totally sums up that special feeling and I cannot wait to wear it in Paris this summer.\\\"  The typeface is said to draw its inspiration from the outfits worn by British athletes at the Paris Olympics in 1924, the last time the city staged the Games.  Britain's most and least affordable towns revealed in Zoopla survey  Inside Olympic swimmer Adam Peaty's stag do as he prepares to marry Holly Ramsay  Which countries are illegal migrants coming from as UK issues visa ban threat?  The best destinations and activities to book this winter  It comes after theBritish Olympic Associationpromised a traditional approach to its kit aftera backlash over its sale of some Union Flag merchandise in different colours. The Football Association also found itself at the centre of a controversy when Nike changed the colour of the St George's Cross on the collar of the England football team's kit.  Adidas said the \\\"design principles\\\" behind the new Team GB kit would allow athletes to \\\"participate in comfort, and without distraction\\\" - in stark contrast to the Team USA kit, which includes a high-cut leotard branded sexist by some athletes.  MORE ABOUT  Have your say...  1  Football  Arsenal injury update: William Saliba, Cristhian Mosquera and Gabriel latest news and return dates  Arsenal injury update: Saliba, Mosquera, Gabriel latest return dates  2  Football  FA Cup draw LIVE! Arsenal, Manchester United, Chelsea and Tottenham learn third-round fate  FA Cup draw LIVE! Arsenal, Man Utd and Chelsea learn third-round fate  3  Football  Manchester United XI vs Wolves: Starting lineup, confirmed team news, injury latest for Premier League today  Man United XI vs Wolves: Starting lineup and confirmed team news  4  Football  Good news for Arsenal after title setback but now Mikel Arteta must buck trend  Good news for Arsenal after title setback but Arteta must buck trend  5  Football  FA Cup third round draw in full: Arsenal handed away tie, Man Utd face Brighton as Tottenham get Aston Villa  FA Cup third round draw in full as Arsenal get Portsmouth\"}"